  "notes": [
    "Schedule A (Form 1040) AcroForm widget map for the IRS-hosted TY2025 PDF (PDF /Title metadata is '2025 Schedule A (Form 1040)'). The IRS has already published the TY2025 fillable form at the canonical URL.",
    "Widget enumeration walks /Annots on each page (NOT reader.get_fields(), which over-reports non-terminal containers). Sorted into visual reading order (page asc, rect_top desc, rect_left asc) before correlation.",
    "TY2024-vs-TY2025 deltas: none observed for Schedule A line layout. Lines 1-17 match TY2024 verbatim. Line 5e SALT cap is permanent under OBBBA (was scheduled to sunset post-TY2025 under TCJA \u2014 see skill/scripts/calc/engine.SALT_CAP_NORMAL).",
    "Schedule A uses TWO amount columns: an INTERMEDIATE column (x ~410-481) for sublines that feed into a section subtotal (e.g. 5a, 5b, 5c, 5d, 5e, 8a-8e, etc.) and a GRAND column (x ~504-576) for section subtotals that flow into line 17 (lines 4, 7, 10, 14, 15, and 17 itself). The widget map preserves this distinction in the rect coordinates.",
    "Three widgets that pair a left-wide text descriptor with an amount input are scaffolded as 'descriptor' unmapped: f1_12 (line 6 descriptor), f1_16 (line 8b name/address), f1_28 (line 16 descriptor). Layer 1 ScheduleAFields only carries the amount; populating the descriptor is a follow-up.",
    "Layer 1 stores 'filing_status' as a string but Schedule A has no filing-status widgets \u2014 the filing status is carried over from Form 1040. Likewise the SSN widget f1_2 is unmapped because Layer 1 does not duplicate the Form 1040 SSN here."
  ],
